                <note rend="inline" type="source">883.6363/25: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Howell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-02-23T15:00:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 23, 1927—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 23—12:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>7. Your telegram No. 4, February 4th [<hi rend="italic">3rd</hi>]. Investigation
                    discloses no direct action upon part of British and Belgian colleagues.<note
                        n="27" xml:id="d640fn27">In his telegram No. 8, Feb. 25, 1927, 9 a.m. (file
                        No. 883.6363/27), the Minister stated: “Belgian colleague represents
                        Roumanian interests”.</note> Latter favorable to joint action. British
                    considering what steps if any should be taken. They seemed impressed with the
                    irregularities pointed out and indicated arguments to be used in justice to
                    companies complying with the law and danger to plants operated by these
                    companies. It is believed floating storage with little investment has caused
                    petroleum products to be sold at a lower figure than would otherwise obtain.
                    Recommend that no further action be taken until the British reply to my
                    memorandum left with the High Commissioner.<note n="28" xml:id="d640fn28">Copy
                        not found in Department files.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Howell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
